natural problem: Javier is biking at 15 miles per hour. There are 5280 feet in a mile. How many feet does he travel in one minute?
natural solution: Since 15 miles per hour is 1/4 mile per minute, Javier travels $(5280)(1/4) = \boxed{1320}$ feet in one minute.
